spanishExample: ¡Sal! Es un hecho que la espera es mala.
englishTranslation: Go out! It’s a fact that the wait is bad.

spanishExample: ¡Salga! Parece que quiere hacer algo.
englishTranslation: (Formal) Go out! It seems like you want to do something.

spanishExample: ¡Salgan! De hecho, ese es el trato.
englishTranslation: (Plural) Go out! In fact, that is the deal.

spanishExample: Creo, de hecho, que no saldrá con él.
englishTranslation: I think, indeed, that she won’t go out with him.

spanishExample: Diez menos ocho son, de hecho, dos.
englishTranslation: Ten minus eight is, indeed, two.

spanishExample: El hecho es que la espera no pareció mala.
englishTranslation: The fact is that the wait didn’t seem bad.

spanishExample: El hecho es que nueve más uno es igual a diez.
englishTranslation: The fact is that nine plus one equals to ten.

spanishExample: Esta espera es mala porque teníamos un trato y era a las diez.
englishTranslation: This wait is bad because we had a deal and it was at ten.

spanishExample: Este hecho es, de hecho, muy importante.
englishTranslation: This occurrence is, indeed, very important.

spanishExample: Le parecía un hecho, pero ese no era el trato.
englishTranslation: It seemed like a fact to him, but that wasn’t the deal.

spanishExample: Llámala porque está, de hecho, a la espera.
englishTranslation: Call her because she is, in fact, in waiting.

spanishExample: No hemos salido, pero dime si llama.
englishTranslation: We haven’t gone out, but tell me if he calls.

spanishExample: No quiero que salgan este fin de semana.
englishTranslation: I don’t want them to go out this weekend.

spanishExample: No salimos porque no tuvimos control.
englishTranslation: We didn’t go out because we didn’t have control.

spanishExample: Nunca salgo porque puede parecer un hecho malo.
englishTranslation: I never go out because it might seem like a bad act.

spanishExample: Parecen tener control y quieren llamar a la puerta.
englishTranslation: They seem to have control and they want to knock on the door.

spanishExample: Quiere que salgamos antes de las ocho.
englishTranslation: She wants us to go out before eight.

spanishExample: Salió porque no quería estar a la espera.
englishTranslation: He went out because he didn’t want to be in waiting.

spanishExample: Si me llamas antes de las nueve, podemos salir a las diez.
englishTranslation: If you call me before nine, we can go out at ten.

spanishExample: Siempre la llamo, pero nunca sale.
englishTranslation: I always call her, but she never goes out.

spanishExample: Tengo esto bajo control, ocho más uno son nueve.
englishTranslation: I have this under control, eight plus one is nine.

spanishExample: Teníamos un trato, de hecho, estoy esperando.
englishTranslation: We had a deal; in fact, I’m waiting.

spanishExample: Tienes que llamarme porque no me has llamado desde ese trato malo.
englishTranslation: You have to call me because you haven’t called me since that bad treatment.
